# FORGE.md — Project Rules for Forge Agent

> Copy this file to your project root and customize.

## Project Overview

Describe your project here so Forge understands the codebase.

## Architecture

```yaml
architecture:
  layers:
    - types
    - config
    - repository
    - service
    - handler
  cross_cutting:
    - util
    - common
```

## Permissions

```yaml
permissions:
  deny:
    - tool: bash
      pattern: "rm\\s+-rf"
    - tool: bash
      pattern: "sudo"
    - tool: edit_file
      path: "\\.lock$"
    - tool: edit_file
      path: "\\.env$"
  ask:
    - tool: bash
    - tool: git_commit
  allow:
    - tool: read_file
    - tool: search_code
    - tool: list_directory
    - tool: git_status
    - tool: git_diff
    - tool: git_log
```

## Lint

```yaml
lint:
  command: "ruff check ."
  auto_fix_command: "ruff check --fix ."

structural:
  max_file_lines: 500
  max_function_lines: 80
  naming:
    files: snake_case
    classes: PascalCase
  forbidden_patterns:
    - pattern: "print\\("
      exclude: ["cli.py", "terminal_ui.py"]
      message: "Use logging instead of print()"
    - pattern: "TODO(?!\\s*\\[feat-)"
      message: "TODO must reference a feature ID, e.g. TODO [feat-001]"
```

## Conventions

- Use `read_file` before editing any file.
- Run tests after every change.
- One feature at a time.
- Prefer explicit over implicit.
